# UI thrash guardrails

Status like `"Connecting now…"`, `"Connecting…"`, `"Initializing Sockets…"` must never remount/animate in a tight loop.

- Latch/cooldown/ref: retry `setState` at most once per user intent or sane interval
- No sub-second thrash of the same status text
- Stable effect deps — no rapidly changing objects/functions unless memoized or read via refs
- When status spams: stop the retry loop first, then touch UI
